0and%20May.%20Unemployment%20has%20been%20consistently%20low%2C%20hovering%20between%204%25%20and%204.2%25%20since%20May%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-script%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20data-styles%3D%5C%22default-width%5C%22%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22custom%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FWAvbf%2F38%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22US%20unemployment%20rate%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22426%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3ELabor%20force%20participation%20continued%20to%20decline%2C%20falling%20to%2062.2%25%20in%20July%20from%2062.3%25.%20The%20employment-population%20ratio%20also%20ticked%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMarc%20Goldwein%20of%20the%20Committee%20for%20a%20Responsible%20Federal%20Budget%20said%20in%20a%20post%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2FMarcGoldwein%2Fstatus%2F1951263446671974433%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EX%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%26quot%3Ball%2073%2C000%20new%20jobs%20in%20July%20were%20in%20health%20care%20and%20social%20services%26quot%3B%20on%20net.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEmployment%20rose%20by%2055%2C400%20in%20healthcare%20from%20June%20to%20July.%20Employment%20fell%20in%20a%20few%20sectors%2C%20including%20manufacturing%20and%20professional%20and%20business%20services.%20Employment%20fell%20by%2012%2C000%20in%20the%20federal%20government.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAverage%20earnings%20rose%20from%20%2435.07%20an%20hour%20in%20July%202024%20to%20%2436.44%20an%20hour%2C%20a%203.9%25%20increase%20from%20a%20year%20ago.%20Year-over-year%20growth%20in%20average%20hourly%20earnings%20has%20been%20hovering%20between%203.8%25%20and%203.9%25%20since%20January.%20Earnings%20rose%200.3%25%20over%20the%20month%2C%20compared%20to%200.2%25%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20Bureau%20of%20Labor%20Statistics%20report%20is%20just%20one%20of%20several%20economic%20releases%20this%20week.%20Data%20released%20on%20Wednesday%20showed%20real%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A