roduced%20new%20incentives%20for%20companies%20to%20self-report%20misconduct.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECompanies%20that%20quickly%20tell%20the%20DOJ%2C%20cooperate%2C%20and%20handle%20the%20issue%20internally%20can%20breathe%20easy.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20policy%20takes%20some%20risk%20off%20the%20table%20for%20telling%20the%20government%20about%20in-house%20crime.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20Matthew%20Galeotti%2C%20the%20head%20of%20the%20Department%20of%20Justice's%20criminal%20division%2C%20gave%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.justice.gov%2Fopa%2Fspeech%2Fhead-justice-departments-criminal-division-matthew-r-galeotti-delivers-remarks-american%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Espeech%3C%2Fa%3E%20outlining%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20law%20enforcement%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAbout%20halfway%20through%2C%20Galeotti%20used%20a%20word%20that%20ricocheted%20through%20the%20offices%20of%20white-collar%20lawyers%20around%20the%20country%3A%20%26quot%3Bwill.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Justice%20Department%20was%20announcing%20that%20it%20would%20provide%20declination%20letters%20%E2%80%94%20formal%20commitments%20not%20to%20prosecute%20companies%20%E2%80%94%20to%20companies%20that%20turn%20in%20their%20employees%20for%20potential%20white%20collar%20crimes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20the%20second%20Trump%20administration%2C%20there%20was%20only%20a%20%26quot%3Bpresumption%26quot%3B%20of%20a%20declination.%20The%20Justice%20Department%20had%20signaled%20it%20was%20safe%20for%20companies%20to%20self-report%20potential%20crimes%20or%20misconduct%2C%20but%20it%20still%20retained%20the%20discretion%20to%20prosecute%20if%20it%20wanted%20to%2C%20according%20to%20Lisa%20Zornberg%2C%20an%20attorney%20at%20Morvillo%20Abramowitz%20and%20former%20federal%20prosecutor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20one%20word%20%E2%80%94%20will%20%E2%80%94%20replaced%20years%20of%20ambiguity%20with%20a%20guarantee.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGaleotti%20told%20BI%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20his%20revisions%20to%20the%20policy%20maximize%20the%20criminal%20division's%20enforcement%20efforts%20by%20encouraging%20companies%20to%20voluntarily%20self-disclose%20potential%20wrongdoing%2C%20cooperate%20with%20investigations%2C%20and%20%26quot%3Bdisgorge%20ill-gotten%20gains.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20revisions%20in%20May%20to%20our%20Corporate%20Enforcement%20and%20Voluntary%20Self-Disclosure%20Policy%20(CEP)%20provide%20clear%20incentives%20for%20companies%20to%20do%20just%20that%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20Division%20to%20identify%20and%20prosecute%20white%20collar%20crimes%2C%20including%20those%20we%20may%20never%20otherwise%20know%20about%2C%20and%20hold%20individual%20wrongdoers%20accountable%2C%26quot%3B%20Galeotti's%20statement%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20policy%20also%20encourages%20companies%20to%20invest%20in%20compliance%20programs%2C%20which%20helps%20deter%20misconduct%20from%20happening%20in%20the%20first%20place%20and%20detect%20it%20when%20it%20does%20occur%2C%20all%20of%20which%20benefits%20the%20American%20public.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20policy%20offers%20the%20benefit%20of%20certainty%20and%20closure.%20If%20a%20company%20blows%20the%20whistle%20on%20itself%2C%20works%20with%20federal%20authorities%20to%20investigate%20employees%2C%20and%20handles%20the%20situation%20internally%2C%20then%20they%20will%20receive%20a%20declination%20letter%2C%20Galeotti%20said%20in%20his%20June%20speech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20you%20self-report%20and%20you%20get%20a%20declination%2C%20it's%20over%2C%26quot%3B%20Zornberg%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20in%20the%20company's%20rear%20view%20mirror%20and%20you%20don't%20have%20to%20worry%20or%20wonder%20whether%20in%20four%20years%20from%20now%20a%20different%20DOJ%20administration%20is%20going%20to%20come%20back%20and%20dig%20into%20what%20happened.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%223391ff50-477a-4caa-aa2b-e1b0b4aa666c%5C%22%3ESelf-reporting%20isn't%20always%20the%20obvious%20move%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20receive%20a%20declination%2C%20the%20companies%20need%20to%20cooperate%20with%20the%20government%2C%20which%20could%20mean%20supplying%20information%20to%20pursue%20criminal%20charges%20or%20civil%20enforcement%20action%20against%20any%20employees%20responsible%20for%20the%20mess.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThey're%20trying%20to%20take%20a%20narrower%20view%20of%20when%20the%20corporation%20has%20to%20be%20prosecuted%2C%20and%20instead%20they're%20going%20to%20focus%20on%20individual%20wrongdoers%2C%26quot%3B%20Zornberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20corporations%2C%20recognizing%20wrongdoing%20%E2%80%94%20like%20fraud%2C%20bribery%2C%20or%20skirting%20regulations%20%E2%80%94%20and%20reporting%20it%20to%20the%20government%20isn't%20always%20a%20black-and-white%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20companies%20conduct%20an%20internal%20investigation%20into%20potential%20criminal%20activity%2C%20they%20face%20a%20sophisticated%20decision%20matrix%20for%20how%20to%20move%20forward.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDo%20they%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20government%20when%20they%20open%20the%20investigation%2C%20before%20all%20the%20facts%20are%20known%3F%20If%20they%20suspect%20a%20whistleblower%2C%20do%20they%20want%20to%20rush%20to%20self-report%20before%20the%20whistleblower%20goes%20public%3F%20What%20if%20they're%20unsure%20if%20there%20was%20a%20civil%20or%20criminal%20offense%2C%20or%20simply%20a%20violation%20of%20an%20internal%20company%20policy%3F%20And%20are%20they%20sure%20the%20Justice%20Department%20would%20even%20be%20interested%20in%20the%20misconduct%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BDeciding%20whether%20and%20when%20to%20self-report%20is%20not%20off%20the%20rack%2C%20it's%20couture%2C%26quot%3B%20Zornberg%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETurning%20in%20your%20own%20employees%20to%20the%20government%20could%20have%20downsides.%20While%20it's%20helpful%20for%20agencies%2C%20it%20could%20be%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20interests%20of%20shareholders%20or%20employees%2C%20according%20to%20Rod%20Rosenstein%2C%20who%20served%20as%20deputy%20attorney%20general%20in%20the%20first%20Trump%20administration.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECompanies%20have%20fiduciary%20obligations%20to%20weigh%20the%20pros%20and%20cons%2C%20Rosenstein%20said.%20Instead%20of%20telling%20the%20government%2C%20they%20could%20try%20to%20fix%20things%20in-house%20and%20hope%20government%20agencies%20don't%20find%20out%20about%20it%20before%20the%20statute%20of%20limitations%20expires%2C%20he%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20Even%20if%20the%20Justice%20Department%20chooses%20not%20to%20prosecute%20a%20case%2C%20there's%20always%20the%20risk%20that%20the%20disclosures%20could%20trigger%20class%20action%20or%20shareholder%20lawsuits%2C%20or%20an%20investigation%20from%20a%20regulator%20in%20another%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFor%20companies%20that%20have%20engaged%20in%20wrongdoing%2C%20there's%20always%20a%20cost-benefit%20analysis%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Rosenstein%2C%20now%20an%20attorney%20at%20Baker%20McKenzie.%20%26quot%3BAs%20in%2C%20'If%20we%20say%20nothing%2C%20there's%20a%20chance%20we'll%20get%20away%20with%20it.%20If%20we%20cooperate%2C%20how%20harsh%20a%20penalty%20are%20we%20going%20to%20suffer%3F%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20second%20Trump%20administration%20has%20taken%20a%20light%20touch%20on%20white%20collar%20crime%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgovernment-lawyers-white-collar-job-search-difficult-trump-policies-2025-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eas%20Business%20Insider%20previously%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20increasing%20incentives%20for%20self-reporting%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20can%20enforce%20the%20laws%20with%20fewer%20resources%2C%20Rosenstein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20perception%20of%20reduced%20enforcement%20does%20create%20a%20risk%20that%20companies%20will%20be%20more%20willing%20to%20roll%20the%20dice%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenstein%20said.%20%26quot%3BAnd%20so%20this%20policy%20is%20really%20intended%20to%20offset%20that%20to%20some%20extent%20by%20creating%20a%20greater%2C%20a%20bigger%20carrot%20to%20incentivize%20companies%20to%20come%20forward%20and%20cooperate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22dd8187f3-a234-414e-86f3-0914c1c982a4%5C%22%3EThe%20DOJ%20is%20upping%20the%20incentives%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20companies%20that%20report%20their%20own%20misconduct%20and%20cooperate%20with%20the%20government%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20also%20created%20incentives%20for%20companies%20that%20exist%20in%20a%20gray%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20May%2C%20it%20announced%20that%20companies%20won't%20necessarily%20face%20a%20full-scale%20criminal%20investigation%20if%20they%20don't%20do%20everything%20they%20need%20to%20do%20to%20get%20a%20declination%20letter.%20If%20a%20company%20self-reports%20but%20doesn't%20do%20so%20quickly%20enough%2C%20or%20if%20there%20are%20aggravating%20factors%20that%20could%20still%20warrant%20a%20criminal%20prosecution%2C%20the%20Justice%20Department%20says%20it'll%20offer%20a%20non-prosecution%20agreement%20and%20reduced%20fines.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Rosenstein%2C%20the%20incentives%20continue%20a%20decadeslong%20effort%20by%20both%20Democratic%20and%20Republican%20administrations%20to%20make%20it%20easier%20for%20companies%20to%20self-report%20suspected%20crimes%20being%20committed%20within%20companies..%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20government%20has%20adopted%20a%20series%20of%20strategies%20to%20try%20to%20incentivize%20companies%20to%20police%20themselves%20and%20report%20to%20the%20government%20the%20details%20of%20the%20wrongdoing%2C%26quot%3B%20Rosenstein%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20also%20marks%20a%20continuation%20of%20the%20Justice%20Department%20going%20after%20individual%20bad%20actors%2C%20rather%20than%20entire%20corporations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EProsecuting%20an%20entire%20company%20could%20be%20a%20death%20knell%20for%20the%20corporation%2C%20potentially%20leading%20to%20people%20unaffiliated%20with%20the%20wrongdoing%20losing%20their%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20corporation%20is%20in%20some%20ways%20a%20fiction%2C%26quot%3B%20Zornberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BIf%20you%20prosecute%20a%20corporation%2C%20there's%20almost%20never%20a%20trial%20because%20there's%20no%20one%20to%20sit%20at%20the%20counsel%20table.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EZornberg%20pointed%20to%20the%202002%20conviction%20of%20accounting%20giant%20Arthur%20Andersen%2C%20which%20prosecutors%20said%20enabled%20fraud%20at%20Enron.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20overturned%20the%20company's%20conviction%20three%20years%20later%2C%20but%20Arthur%20Anderson%20had%20already%20collapsed%20by%20then%2C%20leading%20to%20tens%20of%20thousands%20of%20job%20losses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BFrom%20a%20prosecutor's%20standpoint%2C%20it%20just%20hits%20in%20the%20moral%20kishkas%20that%2C%20if%20there%20are%20individuals%20who%20have%20been%20engaged%20in%20criminal%20conduct%20%E2%80%94%20flesh%20and%20blood%20people%20who%20have%20done%20wrong%20things%20that%20have%20injured%20investors%20or%20the%20environment%20or%20whatever%2C%20name%20your%20victim%20%E2%80%94%20that%20those%20individuals%20should%20be%20held%20accountable%20for%20their%20conduct%2C%26quot%3B%20Zornberg%20said.%20%26quot%3BThat's%20the%20ethos%20of%20always%20prioritizing%20the%20accountability%20of%20individuals.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-self-report-crime-misconduct-justice-department-policy-2025-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1754039522000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F688b7883f748d8c055f69f86%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcompanies-self-report-crime-misconduct-justice-department-policy-2025-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Ju